      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add Silmaril Firewall tool-result middleware",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nSilmaril post-execution blocking parity needs an OpenClaw host-enforceable boundary for tool results before OpenClaw/Codex agents reuse those results as model context. External OpenClaw plugins can observe `tool_result_persist`, but they cannot register agent tool-result middleware, so OpenClaw needs a bundled extension that owns the native `agentToolResultMiddleware` contract for the current OpenClaw and Codex runtimes.\n\n## Summary\n\n- add a bundled, manifest-only `silmaril-firewall` extension for OpenClaw/Codex agent tool-result middleware\n- classify text tool results and replace malicious results with safe metadata when existing `blockMalicious` is enabled and `shadowMode` is off\n- avoid new runtime dependency graph changes by using a small direct Silmaril `/classify` client instead of adding an SDK package\n- add manifest/middleware tests, labeler coverage, changelog entry, and refreshed docs map\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `CI=true pnpm install --frozen-lockfile --ignore-scripts`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extensions.config.ts extensions/silmaril-firewall`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs --threads=8`\n- `pnpm lint:extensions:bundled`\n- `CI=true pnpm tsgo:prod && CI=true pnpm tsgo:test`\n- `pnpm check:docs && node scripts/generate-docs-map.mjs --check`\n- `pnpm test:extensions:package-boundary`\n- `node scripts/run-additional-boundary-checks.mjs`\n- `pnpm test:contracts:plugins`\n- Net PR diff excludes `pnpm-lock.yaml` and `extensions/silmaril-firewall/package.json` to avoid external dependency graph changes.",
